=Luminous is a syntax highlighter for PHP!=

Luminous is a powerful and accurate multi-language PHP syntax highlighter for the modern web. It's written in PHP, and can highlight a wide selection of common [page/languages languages]. It can generate HTML and LaTeX output, and is fully styleable via CSS. It also includes a built in cache, so your server shouldn't get too exhausted.

Read more about its [page/features features], try out some [demo online highlighting], or [download download] it.

==News==
\feed http://blog.luminous.asgaard.co.uk/feed/ 2


==Short example==
{{{lang=php
<?php require_once('luminous/luminous.php'); ?>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <?= luminous::head_html(); ?>
  </head>
  <body>
  <?= luminous::highlight('php', 'echo "hello world";'); ?>
  </body>
</html>
}}}